Rejected Ideas
Deep learning (LSTM, CNN) on raw sensor streams: Requires far more data and computational resources; OCSVM on engineered features is more suitable for the current dataset size.

Global two‑class model: Impostor data across users is device‑specific; pooling it introduces bias.

Hard feature selection (RFE): Too slow and not inherently better than the consensus ranking.

Using only one ranking method: Early tests showed that different methods favoured different feature groups; a consensus was necessary to avoid bias.

